    <div class="section">
        <h2>Top Strengths: Survey Showdown Stars</h2>
        <p>I'm pumped to highlight these ‚Äòmention‚Äô wins. Here's where guests think we‚Äôre excelling:</p>
        <ol>
            <li><span class="emoji">üî•</span> <strong>Host Performance</strong> (50 mentions): Common praises for Andreas (funny, smooth), Juno (fantastic, engaging), Hailey (awesome for groups), Kali (explanatory, light-hearted), Faith (hilarious) and others like Anya/Shea (welcoming, showman-like). <span class="quote">"The host was fantastic!"</span></li>
            <li><span class="emoji">üëØ‚Äç‚ôÇÔ∏èüèÜ</span> <strong>Fun and Unique Experience</strong> (~90 mentions): Described as ‚Äúunique,‚Äù ‚Äúinteractive,‚Äù and ‚Äúa blast,‚Äù ideal for families, friends, and teams. Games like Family Feud and Wheel of Fortune were highlights. <span class="quote">"It felt like I was on a game show like on tv!! Loved it."</span></li>
            <li><span class="emoji">üéØüé¨</span> <strong>Atmosphere and Production</strong> (~30 mentions): Lighting, decor, and buzzers created a TV-worthy experience. <span class="quote">"We loved the atmosphere of the game show! Lighting was nice large screens and even the podiums and the buzzers were nice."</span></li>
            <li><span class="emoji">üåü</span> <strong>Unique Edge</strong>: 80% say we're better than most entertainment options.</li>
        </ol>
        <p>These strengths position Game Show Studios as a leader in interactive entertainment.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>Audience Feedback: Qualitative Insights</h2>
        <ol>
            <li><span class="emoji">‚è∞</span> <strong>Duration and Pace</strong> (45% say too short, ~45 mentions): The 1-hour session felt ‚Äútoo short‚Äù or ‚Äúrushed,‚Äù especially for larger groups. 90-minute options desired. <span class="quote">"I wish it was longer than an hour. It felt like as soon as we started having the most fun, it was over."</span></li>
            <li><span class="emoji">üé≤</span> <strong>Game Tweaks</strong> (~38 mentions): The Over Under game was disliked for random items, duels were seen as unfair or unclear, buzzers felt underutilized, and multiple suggestions of adding more game variety like Trivia. <span class="quote">"Over Under - it was ridiculous items to price."</span></li>
            <li><span class="emoji">‚öôÔ∏è</span> <strong>Technical Issues</strong> (~15 mentions): AC, Sound system problems, game crashes, and scoring confusion impacted professionalism. <span class="quote">"The sound system was horrible couldn‚Äôt hear well the sound was muffled."</span></li>
            <li><span class="emoji">üí∞</span> <strong>Value and Price</strong> (~10 mentions): Some felt the cost was high for the duration, particularly for private parties. <span class="quote">"Pricing. We all felt it was way too expensive for just 1h of game."</span></li>
        </ol>
        <p>Other suggestions included: Chairs for players and or spectators who can‚Äôt stand for long periods of time, adding laugh tracks, videos to take home, and selling drinks/snacks.</p>
        <p>These insights highlight areas for improvement to enhance future guest satisfaction.</p>
    </div>

