    <div class="section">
        <h2>DOGI Recommendations</h2>
        <p>Based on data analysis, the following recommendations are proposed to drive growth and improve the guest experience. Let's aim for NPS 80+ with these game-changers:</p>
        <div class="recommendation">
            <p><strong>Extend GSS Duration</strong>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Rationale:</strong> The most frequent complaint is the 1-hour session feeling ‚Äútoo short.‚Äù Longer sessions could improve value perception.</li>
                    <li><strong>Action:</strong> Offer 90-minute upgrade options, especially for larger groups or private parties, to allow more gameplay and engagement.</li>
                </ul>
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="recommendation">
            <p><strong>Refine Game Design</strong>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Rationale:</strong> Over Under and duels received criticism for being unengaging or unfair. Adding variety (e.g., trivia) could boost appeal.</li>
                    <li><strong>Action:</strong> Revamp or remove Over Under, ensure fair and inclusive duels, add trivia rounds, increase buzzer use, and allow game choice flexibility.</li>
                </ul>
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="recommendation">
            <p><strong>Address Technical Issues</strong>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Rationale:</strong> Technical problems (sound, crashes, scoring) were noted in ~15 responses, particularly in San Diego, impacting professionalism.</li>
                    <li><strong>Action:</strong> Invest in reliable audio/video systems, add mics to podiums, and ensure pre-session checks to prevent disruptions.</li>
                </ul>
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="recommendation">
            <p><strong>Enhance Perceived Value</strong>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Rationale:</strong> Price concerns (~15 mentions) suggest the cost feels high for the duration or experience. Added features could justify pricing.</li>
                    <li><strong>Action:</strong> Offer take-home prizes, optional video recordings, or drink bundles. Test off-peak discounts to reduce 19% "pricey" perception.</li>
                </ul>
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>

